Url.Title: System 1 Fleet Management Introduction
Url.Abstract: System 1 Fleet Management Introduction GE's System 1 Fleet Management is a Web-based software application (portal) for monitoring and diagnosing the overall health of your Fleet. A Fleet is comprised of Sites, Folders, Trains, and Machines.

Url.Title: About this Online Help
Url.Abstract: The System 1 Fleet Management User GuideOnline Help provides comprehensive instructions about how to use the System 1 Fleet Management Web application.

Url.Title: Getting Started
Url.Abstract: Getting Started This section explains how to start using System 1 Fleet Management and how to logout after a session.

Url.Title: Dashboard
Url.Abstract: Introducing the Dashboard Module The Dashboard module is displayed by default after you log in to System 1 Fleet Management. The Dashboard provides icons and controls that you can use to navigate the System 1 Fleet Management portal. The main feature of the Dashboard is the grid view table. The table displays health index data about the sites, folders, trains, and machines in a selected customer's Fleet. The following figure shows an example of a typical Dashboard module that is similar to one you might view after logging in.

Url.Title: Viewing and Sorting Gauge Alarm Overview Graphics
Url.Abstract: Working With the Gauges The Gauges view on the Overview page shows the health of the site, folder, train, machine and more.

Url.Title: Changing the Index Threshold Values
Url.Abstract: Changing the Index Threshold Values System 1 Fleet uses index threshold values to color-code the health status of enterprises, folders and nodes in Health Index View. Customers can configure different threshold values for each enterprise.

Url.Title: Alarms and Events

Url.Title: Understanding Alarm Severity Designations
Url.Abstract: About Alarm Severity Designations This section describes the legacy method of how System 1 and SmartSignal designated alarm severity, and the new method used by System 1 Fleet Management to designate System 1 and SmartSignal alarm severity.

Url.Title: Exporting a Table
Url.Abstract: Exporting Alarm Table Data You can export the data that is in the Alarm Table and save the data in to a .csv file.

Url.Title: Adding an Enterprise
Url.Abstract: Generating bar Charts The bar chart shows the quantity of alarms and their associated severity for a selected item, which can be Enterprise, Folder, Train, or Machine. The bars in the chart are organized by the normalized severity colors.

Url.Title: Adding an Enterprise
Url.Abstract: Generating Line Charts Use the Line Chart generation feature on the Alarms tab to create line charts that show alarm trends for different enterprises in a selected fleet and hierarchy. You can hold the mouse over a point in the chart for a few seconds and view the number of alarm(s) that occurred on the date the alarm occurred.

Url.Title: Copying a Table
Url.Abstract: Printing or Saving a Chart or Plot You have the option to save or print an alarm bar or line chart or a plot.

Url.Title: Describing the Alarms List Table
Url.Abstract: Using the Alarms List Filter Feature You can filter the data displayed in the Alarm List and in the bar, line and alarm plots by filtering on one or more data points in the Alarm List table columns.

Url.Title: Showing and Hiding Columns in Alarms Table
Url.Abstract: Selecting Columns for the Alarm Table The information in the Alarms List table depends on the columns chosen for display.

Url.Title: Viewing Analysis Statistics
Url.Abstract: Generating an Analysis Plot An analysis plot displays a plot generated by selecting variables for a specific time and date interval for a selected machine or train. The Analysis Plot feature is only available for static variables in System 1. After you generate an Analysis plot, you can save and retrieve plot session endpoint and variable settings in the database. You can print an analysis plot, or save the plot as a .PNG graphic file.

Url.Title: Viewing and Editing Your Preference Settings
Url.Abstract: Editing Preferences You have the option to modify a subset of default Preferences settings on the General Settings, Overview Page, and Alarms Page.

Url.Title: Editing General Preferences
Url.Abstract: Editing General Preferences In this section of the Preferences page, you can modify Time Zone, Auto-Refresh, and Primary Hierarchy settings. The following figure shows the General preference settings.

Url.Title: Viewing Your Account Profile
Url.Abstract: Editing Your Account Profile The Account Profile pane displays your Username, Role, Name, and Email address. You can change your Name and email address. Depending on system configuration, the Account Profile page might include the option to change the password for your account.

Url.Title: Administering Users
Url.Abstract: Administration Module The System 1 Fleet Management administrator is responsible for managing users, activating and deactivating enterprises, and mapping System 1 Fleet and SmartSignal Assets. Click the Administration module on the Dashboard. The module opens to the Users tab (see following figure).

Url.Title: Editing Users
Url.Abstract: Editing a User To edit the properties of a current's user account settings, follow these steps: Depending on System 1 Fleet Management configuration, you might see a Change Password link. Url.Title: Mapping a Smart Signal System
Url.Abstract: Mapping System 1 and SmartSignal Machines. The Mapping feature allows administrators to correlate data from identical assets that are being monitored simultaneously by System 1 and SmartSignal. System 1 and SmartSignal use different naming conventions to identify the same assets.

Url.Title: Overview Table Index View Column Names
Sorting Information in the Grid View
Url.Abstract: Sorting Information in the Grid View Table To the right of each column row heading is an arrow that allows you to re-sort the default order of the column. The sort order of the Total Alarms column reflects the settings on the User Preference page. If you re-sort the column, the Total Alarms column displays alarms from the highest to the lowest.
